    "answer": "$H_0(\\Sigma_g) \\cong \\mathbb{Z},\\quad H_1(\\Sigma_g) \\cong \\mathbb{Z}^{2g},\\quad H_2(\\Sigma_g) \\cong \\mathbb{Z},\\quad H_n = 0 \\text{ for } n \\geq 3.$",
    "steps": [
      "CW structure: one 0-cell $v$, generators $a_1, b_1, \\ldots, a_g, b_g$ (each a loop at $v$), and one 2-cell attached by $a_1 b_1 a_1^{-1} b_1^{-1} \\cdots a_g b_g a_g^{-1} b_g^{-1}$.",
      "$d_1 = 0$: all 1-cells are loops at $v$.",
      "$d_2(e) = 0$: each $a_i$ (resp.\\ $b_i$) appears once with $+$ sign and once with $-$ sign in the word, giving net coefficient 0.",
      "$H_2 = \\mathbb{Z}$ (generated by the fundamental class $[e]$).",
      "$H_1 = \\mathbb{Z}^{2g}$, freely generated by $[a_1], [b_1], \\ldots, [a_g], [b_g]$.",
      "For $g = 0$: $\\Sigma_0 = S^2$, giving $H_1 = 0$ and $H_2 = \\mathbb{Z}$. ✓"
